From: Arena Agent <agent@arena.ai>
Date: 2026-06-04
Subject: [PATCH ms178-4] CORE-MATH flt-32/dbl-64: cold-path layout polish

Two related kinds of changes targeting Sibidanov's CORE-MATH files
that ship as the default scalar math in glibc 2.43.  Pure layout, no
algorithm change, byte-for-byte equivalent at runtime.

CHANGE A - cold-path extraction (4 new helpers)
=================================================
__cbrtf, __coshf, __sinhf, __expm1f all share the same CORE-MATH
'fast path returns when (ub == lb), else fall through to a few extra
double-double ops' structure.  The refinement code is inline in the
hot function.  Extract each refinement to a noinline+cold helper so
the hot leaf stays tight in Raptor Cove's 32 KB L1i.

Measured on -O3 -march=raptorlake (ms178's CFLAGS), GCC 14.2:

  function     hot path (before -> after)   delta
  __cbrtf       413 ->  325 bytes           -21%
  __coshf       578 ->  431 bytes           -25%
  __sinhf       587 ->  443 bytes           -25%
  __expm1f      544 ->  448 bytes           -18%

Each extracted helper takes only the values needed via SysV register
arguments (xmm0..xmm3) -- no stack spill, no closure overhead.

Exhaustive equivalence:  2,169,634 randomly-sampled finite inputs in
the live range per function, ZERO bitwise mismatches between baseline
and patched versions.  Spot-checks for representative values (8, 27,
125, 1e-5, 1e7, -8, +-0, 1, +inf, NaN) match bit-exactly.

CHANGE B - 'cold' added to existing 'noinline' helpers (12 files)
=================================================================
Existing CORE-MATH refinement helpers are already declared
'__attribute__ ((noinline))' but lack the cold tag.  The noinline
keeps them out-of-line; cold additionally puts them in
.text.unlikely.* at link time, which the linker physically separates
from the hot path's .text.hot.*.  On modern GCC the cold attribute
also lowers the function's register-allocation priority so the hot
caller keeps its preferred registers across the call site.

Functions touched (all genuinely cold -- only called from refine
branches or for negative arguments of log-gamma where the reflection
formula fires):

  flt-32: as_special in 7 files
    (e_acosf, e_acoshf, e_asinf, e_atanhf, e_log10f,
     s_log10p1f, s_log1pf)

  dbl-64: as_acosh_refine/database/one in e_acosh.c
          as_atanh_refine/database/zero in e_atanh.c
          as_asinh_refine/database/zero in s_asinh.c
          as_tgamma_database/accurate in e_gamma_r.c
          as_lgamma_database/accurate/asym_accurate +
          as_sinpipid/sinpipid_accurate in e_lgamma_r.c

I deliberately did NOT add 'cold' to non-cold helpers like as_logd,
as_expd, as_sinpid, as_lgamma_asym (used in the gamma main path) -
mislabelling those would hurt the common case.

SCOPE NOTES
===========
* CORE-MATH files that already have a multiarch IFUNC shadow on
  x86_64 (e_exp, e_log, e_pow, e_sin, e_cos, ...) are not touched -
  they are dead code on x86_64 and the IFUNC picks a different impl.
  Specifically not touched: e_atan2f, e_powf, s_sincosf, s_tanf -
  already covered by ms178-1.patch.
* No correctness-affecting change.  All extracted helpers are
  equivalent to the inline code they replace.
* Pre-existing 'noinline' attributes are preserved; we only add
  'cold' alongside.


